.TH "TEXTDECODER" "3JS" "June 28, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
TextDecoder \- TextDecoder
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]TextDecoder\f[B]\f[R] interface represents a decoder for
a specific text encoding, such as \f[CR]UTF\-8\f[R],
\f[CR]ISO\-8859\-2\f[R], or \f[CR]GBK\f[R].
A decoder takes an array of bytes as input and returns a JavaScript
string.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.TP
\f[B]TextDecoder()\f[R]
Creates and returns a new \f[CR]TextDecoder\f[R].
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]The \f[CI]TextDecoder\f[I] interface doesn\(cqt inherit any
properties.\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]TextDecoder.encoding\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A string containing the name of the character encoding system that this
\f[CR]TextDecoder\f[R] will use.
.TP
\f[B]TextDecoder.fatal\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A boolean indicating whether the error mode is fatal.
.TP
\f[B]TextDecoder.ignoreBOM\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A boolean indicating whether the \c
.UR https://www.w3.org/International/questions/qa-byte-order-mark
byte order mark
.UE \c
\ is ignored.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]The \f[CI]TextDecoder\f[I] interface doesn\(cqt inherit any
methods\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]TextDecoder.decode()\f[R]
Decodes the given bytes into a JavaScript string and returns it.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Decoding UTF\-8 text
This example shows how to decode the UTF\-8 encoding of the character
\(lq𠮷\(rq.
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqdecode\(dq>Decode</\f[B]button\f[R]>
<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqreset\(dq>Reset</\f[B]button\f[R]>
<\f[B]div\f[R] id=\(dqoutput\(dq></\f[B]div\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] utf8decoder = \f[B]new\f[R] TextDecoder(); \f[I]// default \(aqutf\-8\(aq\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] encodedText = \f[B]new\f[R] Uint8Array([240, 160, 174, 183]);

\f[B]const\f[R] output = document.querySelector(\(dq#output\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] decodeButton = document.querySelector(\(dq#decode\(dq);
decodeButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  output.textContent = utf8decoder.decode(encodedText);
});

\f[B]const\f[R] resetButton = document.querySelector(\(dq#reset\(dq);
resetButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  window.location.reload();
});
.EE
.SS Decoding non\-UTF8 text
In this example, we decode the Russian text \(lqПривет, мир!\(rq, which
means \(lqHello, world.\(rq In our \f[CR]TextDecoder()\f[R] constructor,
we specify the Windows\-1251 character encoding.
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqdecode\(dq>Decode</\f[B]button\f[R]>
<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqreset\(dq>Reset</\f[B]button\f[R]>
<\f[B]div\f[R] id=\(dqdecoded\(dq></\f[B]div\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] win1251decoder = \f[B]new\f[R] TextDecoder(\(dqwindows\-1251\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] encodedText = \f[B]new\f[R] Uint8Array([
  207, 240, 232, 226, 229, 242, 44, 32, 236, 232, 240, 33,
]);

\f[B]const\f[R] decoded = document.querySelector(\(dq#decoded\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] decodeButton = document.querySelector(\(dq#decode\(dq);
decodeButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  decoded.textContent = win1251decoder.decode(encodedText);
});

\f[B]const\f[R] resetButton = document.querySelector(\(dq#reset\(dq);
resetButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  window.location.reload();
});
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
The \f[CR]TextEncoder\f[R] interface describing the inverse operation.
